verse.lines:
{lang-eng}We love Thee for the glorious worth
Which in Thyself we see;
We love Thee for that shameful cross,
Endured so patiently.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}No man of greater love can boast
Than for his friend to die;
Thou for Thine enemies wast slain!
What love with Thine can vie?{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Like Thee in strength, in meekness, love,
In life in ev’ry phase;
From glory into glory changed,
Till we behold Thy face.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}O Lord, we treasure in our hearts
The mem’ry of Thy love;
And ever shall Thy name to us
A grateful odor prove.{/lang-eng}
